<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 8. Map of distribution of Vanhornia in Eurasia. Green spot - V. yurii sp. nov., blue spots - V. leileri, yellow spots - V. quizhouensis, red spot - specimen from South Korea determined as V. eucnemidarum (Choi & Lee, 2012)." , "Figure 7. Vanhornia leileri Hedqvist, 1976 (A, B female C-F male, specimens from Russian Far East) A, C metasoma, ventral view B, D metasomal tergite 6, posterior view E metasoma, dorsal view F metasoma, lateral view." , "Figure 6. Vanhornia leileri Hedqvist, 1976 (female, specimen from Russian Far East) A wings B metasoma, dorsal view C metasoma, lateral view." , "Figure 5. Vanhornia leileri Hedqvist, 1976 (A-F, H-K female G male, specimens from Russian Far East) A habitus, lateral view B right mandible, lateral view C head, dorsal view D head, front view E head, lateral view F antenna G basal part of antenna H head, antero-lateral view I mesosoma, dorsal view J mesosoma, lateral view K metasoma and hind leg, lateral view." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469460" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469459" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469458" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/469457" .

